'''Doctor Geek's Laboratory''' is an audio show created by Dr. Scott Viguié<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctor Geek's Laboratory, Season 1|url=http://amblingbooks.com/books/view/doctor_geek%e2%80%99s_laboratory_season_1|publisher=Ambling Books|accessdate=18 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Star Mage Meets His Match|url=http://www.bleedingcool.com/2014/08/29/the-star-mage-meets-his-match-jc-de-la-torre-talks-the-series-finale-doctor-who-upcoming-projects-and-hollywood-interest/|accessdate=2 September 2014}}</ref> that operates as STEM outreach (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math) and is used by some homeschooling parents as part of their science curriculum.<ref>{{cite web|title=Free Dr. Geek's Lab Printable Pack - Perfect for STEM|url=http://homeschoolgiveaways.com/2014/05/free-dr-geeks-lab-printable-pack-perfect-for-stem/|publisher=Homeschool Giveaways and Freebies|accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref> The show portrays a fictional laboratory populated by humorous characters who are trying to bring about the world of tomorrow today. Most of the episodes include a non-fiction element by interviewing scientists, corporate leaders, and others who are actively working on bleeding edge technology and trying to bring it to the consumer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctor Geek's Lab Season 1 Review and Giveaway|url=http://www.morethanacouponqueen.com/2014/01/DrGeeksLabGIveaway.html|publisher=More Than a Coupon Queen|accessdate=18 June 2014}}</ref> The first season of the show is available as a box set from [[Blackstone Audio]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctor Geek's Laboratory|url=http://www.downpour.com/doctor-geek-s-laboratory-season-1-1|publisher=Downpour|accessdate=18 June 2014}}</ref>

